DOCREF="AP890322-0010"
SELECTOR="A"
SUMMARIZER="D">    

Allegations of police racism and brutality have shaken Minneapolis
following the deaths of two blacks at a drug raid that went awry.
Another incident 10-days later involved a scuffle between police and
blacks at a downtown hotel.

In the first incident, Lloyd Smalley, 71 and Lillian Weiss, 65 were
killed Jan. 25 in a fire that started after police hurled a stun
grenade into their apartment, where others also lived.

In the hotel scuffle, police said they responded to a call of a loud
party.  Partygoers alleged that officers used the term "nigger," and
beat some of them severely enough to require them to seek medical
attention.</SUM>


<SUM
