The Sheriff's Department in Los Angeles attempted to maintain a low
profile following the videotaped beating of Rodney King.  Now, Sheriff
Sherman Block finds his department being carefully scrutinized after
deputies shot four people dead in the space of one month.  Three
deputies were charged with stealing credit cards and there are
allegations that the department is a haven for white supremacist
gangs.

An independent commission that examined the police department
following the King beating found racism, brutality, inadequate
discipline, mismanagement and a "siege mentality" pitting officers
against the community.

Now, critics are calling for the same kind of independent
investigation of the sheriff's department.</SUM>

<SUM
