DOCREF="LA010890-0031"
SELECTOR="A"
SUMMARIZER="D">    

A controversial videotape being shown among activists nationwide shows
Los Angeles police officers intentionally hurting the nonviolent
demonstrators they are arresting.

They press fingers under their noses.  They dig their knuckles into
protesters' necks and torque martial arts weapons around their wrists.

The law enforcement name for these techniques is "pain-compliance."
But opponents call the term a euphemism for torture.  One man's arm is
contorted behind his back until it snaps.

Demonstrators have alleged police brutality at least since Freedom
Riders launched their sit-down strikes in Alabama almost 30 years ago.

Police Chief Daryl Gates stands behind the painful tactics used by his
department.</SUM>

<SUM
