In-mid June, a lawsuit against the Los Angeles Police Department was
settled when police agreed to stop using a martial-arts weapon,
nunchakus, against anti-abortion advocates.

Hundreds have charged that police have used excessive force in 50
cities across the United States against demonstrators, most associated
with Operation Rescue, intent on closing down abortion clinics.

The settlement over police use of nunchakus and other painful tactics
against anti- abortion demonstrators receive little attention from
civil right groups, the public or the press.  That may reflect a lack
of public support for groups who attempt to close facilities to deny
the rights of others.</SUM>

<SUM
