A white Long Beach police officer that allegedly pushed a black man
through a plate- glass window during an arrest that was videotaped
acknowledged Friday in a hearing that he made errors in his official
report.  He blamed the discrepancies on a faulty memory, saying he
wrote the report three hours after the incident.

Sen. Daniel Boatwright, Chairman of the Senate Select Committee on
State Procurement and Expenditure Practices, called the hearing into
the incident to review allegations of police misconduct in Long
Beach. The legislative committee monitors state funds disbursed to
police departments by the state Police Officer Standards and Training
Commission.</SUM>

