In Kansas City, Terry D. Barnes, 24, was shot between the eyes in his
own apartment when police mistook him for a burglar. This incident is
one more strike against a police force already struggling with
allegations of brutality and racism.

In June, several white officers bloodied a Nigerian-born Roman
Catholic priest with nightsticks as he lay on the ground.  In May,
another black clergyman was hit on the head with a shotgun by a white
officer while lying on the ground.

Police Chief Steven Bishop said that the department's standing has
fallen in the community, and a "behavior modification" program is
being developed for offending officers.</SUM>

<SUM
