Over the past two years, the Ventura County district attorney's office
in four separate incidents has declined to prosecute suspects who
contended that they were victims of police brutality while being
arrested for various offenses by Oxnard officers.  A fifth man was
charged with a misdemeanor.

Three of the five men have filed police brutality lawsuits against the
city, the department or the police officers involved.

Assistant Police Chief William Kady declined to discuss the brutality
allegations against the Oxnard officers but he said that the decision
by the district attorney's office not to prosecute the suspects do not
reflect poorly on the department.</SUM>

<SUM
