TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="WSJ910405-0154"
SELECTOR="A"
SUMMARIZER="D">    

The brutal beating of Rodney King by Los Angeles policemen offers
convincing evidence that a code of silence exists within that
department.  Four officers took turns kicking and beating an
unresisting victim for more than two minutes.  These criminals in
uniform would not have dared their brutality had they feared that any
of the 17 others officers watching would report their criminal
actions.

Police Chiefs across the country seem to be just as reluctant to
criticize a fellow chief.  The culture of the department that allowed
the brutalizing of Rodney King was created under Chief Daryl Gates's
leadership.  Yet his fellow police chiefs have remained silent for
years about Mr. Gates.</SUM>
